criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  active carious lesion in middle dentin limited to the occlusal or occluso-proximal
             surfaces of primary molars;

          -  children (male or female) in good general health.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  children who refuse or fail to cooperate with the completion of clinical procedure; -
             teeth without antagonist;

          -  carious lesions in inner half of dentin;

          -  presence of painful symptoms or signs of pulpal changes.
